YELLOW FEVER, SOLDIERS - ECUADOR (02)
*************************************
[Yellow Fever, soldiers - Ecuador (Pastaza} 970729150208
Yellow Fever - Bolivia 970311110918]
[1]
From: "Rossana Prandi" <apostol1@ECUA.NET.ec>
Date: Tue, 29 Jul 1997 17:41:47 -500
Source: Hoy newspaper of Quito (June 29)
In April, three soldiers died with symptoms of an hemorragic fever in a
non-endemic area of yellow fever in Esmeraldas province. Another 200
soldiers presented similar symptoms, of which 68 have been admitted to the
Military Hospital in Quito. All the soldiers had recently been in amazonic
area near the border with Peru.
As of June the cause of the disease has not been established. The first
studies in the Instituto Nacional de Higiene did not show evidence of
flavivirus infection, but yellow fever has not been discarded [as a
diagnosis? - Mod. pc].
There have not been similar cases in the population of the area.
Samples of the three died soldiers are being analyzed at CDC.
All of the soldiers were vaccinated against yellow fever.
Other hypothesis are:
Oropouche fever: Apparently people in Peru near the border with Ecuador
were affected, and all the soldiers came from this area.
Dengue fever: This is an endemic area for classic dengue fever.
I think that Dr Marcelo Aguilar <jproanio@uio.satnet.net> from the
Ministerio de Salud can provide more accurate information.
